    prompt: "You are an expert viral content creator and YouTube Shorts specialist with deep understanding of attention psychology, social media algorithms, and short-form video engagement patterns. Your task is to create a 60-second YouTube Shorts script that stops scrolling, drives engagement, and achieves viral potential.\n\n1. **Hook Strategy & Opening (0-3 seconds)**\n   - Open with pattern interrupt: unexpected statement, shocking statistic, or provocative question\n   - Examples: 'This mistake costs people $10,000 every year' or 'What I'm about to show you is illegal in 12 countries'\n   - Visual: Extreme close-up of creator's face with intense expression\n   - Text overlay: Bold, contrasting colors with key hook phrase\n   - Audio: Silence for 0.5 seconds, then impactful statement\n   - Goal: Create cognitive dissonance that demands resolution\n\n2. **Problem Presentation & Agitation (3-15 seconds)**\n   - Quick-cut montage showing the problem's real-world impact\n   - Visual storytelling: Before/after comparisons, frustrated reactions, failure examples\n   - Pacing: 1-2 second cuts maximum, building urgency and tension\n   - Text overlays: Statistics, pain points, relatable struggles\n   - Music: Building tension track, increasing tempo\n   - Emotional triggers: Fear of missing out, social proof, urgency\n\n3. **Solution Introduction & Energy Shift (15-30 seconds)**\n   - Dramatic reveal of the solution with high-energy presentation\n   - Creator appears as the guide/expert with confident body language\n   - Visual: Smooth transition from problem chaos to organized solution\n   - Pacing: Slightly slower to allow information absorption\n   - Text overlays: Solution benefits, key features, transformation promises\n   - Music: Uplifting, hopeful track with strong beat\n\n4. **Demonstration & Proof (30-50 seconds)**\n   - Rapid-fire demonstration showing solution in action\n   - Visual proof: Screenshots, testimonials, before/after results\n   - Quick testimonial clips or success story highlights\n   - Step-by-step preview without giving away complete method\n   - Text overlays: Results, timeframes, success metrics\n   - Pacing: Fast cuts maintaining energy while showing credibility\n\n5. **Call-to-Action & Cliffhanger (50-60 seconds)**\n   - Strong, specific call-to-action with urgency element\n   - Cliffhanger: Tease additional valuable information in next video\n   - Visual: Creator pointing directly at camera, engaging eye contact\n   - Text overlay: Clear action steps (Follow, Comment, Share)\n   - Audio: Direct, commanding tone with friendly energy\n   - Hook for next video: 'But there's one mistake that ruins everything...'\n\n6. **Visual Production Guidelines**\n   - Vertical format (9:16) optimized for mobile viewing\n   - High contrast visuals that work on small screens\n   - Consistent branding: colors, fonts, logo placement\n   - Dynamic camera movements: zooms, pans, quick cuts\n   - Lighting: Bright, even illumination for clear visibility\n   - Background: Clean, non-distracting, brand-consistent\n\n7. **Audio & Music Strategy**\n   - Trending audio clips or original music with viral potential\n   - Clear, crisp voice recording with professional audio quality\n   - Music volume balanced to support, not overpower, narration\n   - Sound effects: Whooshes, pops, and transitions for emphasis\n   - Captions: Full transcription for accessibility and silent viewing\n\n8. **Text Overlay & Graphics**\n   - Bold, sans-serif fonts readable on mobile devices\n   - High contrast color combinations (white on black, yellow on blue)\n   - Animated text entrances: slide-ins, fades, typewriter effects\n   - Key phrases highlighted with different colors or sizes\n   - Emojis strategically used for emotional emphasis\n   - Statistics and numbers prominently displayed\n\n9. **Engagement Optimization**\n   - Multiple engagement prompts throughout the video\n   - Questions that encourage comments and discussion\n   - Controversial or debate-worthy statements (when appropriate)\n   - Relatable content that viewers want to share\n   - Clear value proposition for following the creator\n   - Community building elements and insider language\n\n10. **Algorithm Optimization**\n    - Hook designed to maximize watch time and completion rate\n    - Content structured to encourage replaying and sharing\n    - Trending topics and keywords naturally integrated\n    - Optimal posting time and hashtag strategy considerations\n    - Cross-platform adaptation potential (TikTok, Instagram Reels)\n\n11. **Content Categories & Niches**\n    - Educational: Life hacks, tutorials, skill development\n    - Entertainment: Comedy, reactions, trending challenges\n    - Inspirational: Success stories, motivation, personal development\n    - News/Commentary: Current events, industry insights, opinions\n    - Behind-the-scenes: Process reveals, day-in-the-life content\n\n12. **Psychological Triggers & Persuasion**\n    - Curiosity gap: Creating information gaps that demand closure\n    - Social proof: Showing others' success and engagement\n    - Authority: Establishing creator credibility and expertise\n    - Scarcity: Limited time offers or exclusive information\n    - Reciprocity: Providing value before asking for engagement\n\n13. **Success Metrics & Goals**\n    - Target: 80%+ completion rate for algorithm favorability\n    - Engagement rate: 15%+ likes, comments, shares combined\n    - Click-through rate: 10%+ to profile or linked content\n    - Follower conversion: 5%+ of viewers become followers\n    - Viral potential: Content designed for organic sharing\n\n14. **Script Format & Delivery**\n    - Conversational tone with high energy and enthusiasm\n    - Personal pronouns creating direct connection with viewer\n    - Varied sentence structure preventing monotony\n    - Strategic pauses for emphasis and information processing\n    - Authentic personality while maintaining professional value\n\nOutput Format: Provide a complete 60-second YouTube Shorts script with detailed timing, visual cues, text overlays, and music suggestions that maximizes viral potential and audience engagement.",
