    prompt: "You are an expert viral marketing strategist and meme culture specialist with deep understanding of social media psychology, humor theory, and viral content mechanics. Your task is to create the ultimate relatable meme template that brands can customize while maintaining authentic connection with audiences.\n\n1. **Meme Format & Visual Structure**\n   - Split-screen comparison layout with clear visual division\n   - Left panel: 'Expectation' - idealized, aspirational scenario\n   - Right panel: 'Reality' - humorous, authentic truth\n   - Aspect ratio: 1:1 square format for maximum social media compatibility\n   - Clear visual hierarchy directing eye flow from left to right\n   - Consistent styling between panels while showing contrast\n\n2. **Typography & Text Design**\n   - Header text: Bold, sans-serif font (Impact or similar) in white with black outline\n   - Text placement: Top 15% of image for maximum visibility\n   - Font size: Large enough to read on mobile devices (minimum 36pt)\n   - Text contrast: High contrast against any background color\n   - Character limit: Maximum 8-10 words for quick comprehension\n   - Backup text areas: Bottom of image for additional context if needed\n\n3. **Color Psychology & Visual Appeal**\n   - Expectation side: Bright, saturated colors suggesting optimism and aspiration\n   - Reality side: Slightly desaturated or contrasting colors showing authentic experience\n   - Overall palette: Modern, trendy colors that photograph well\n   - Background compatibility: Colors that work with various text overlays\n   - Brand flexibility: Neutral enough for various brand color integration\n   - Accessibility: Sufficient contrast ratios for visually impaired users\n\n4. **Relatable Content Themes**\n   - Work-life balance: Professional expectations vs. actual work experience\n   - Social media: Instagram-perfect life vs. behind-the-scenes reality\n   - Fitness/health: Workout motivation vs. actual exercise struggles\n   - Cooking: Pinterest recipes vs. kitchen disasters\n   - Technology: Product promises vs. user experience reality\n   - Relationships: Dating app profiles vs. actual dating experiences\n\n5. **Visual Storytelling Elements**\n   - Expectation panel: Clean, organized, aspirational imagery\n   - Reality panel: Chaotic, messy, or unexpectedly authentic imagery\n   - Facial expressions: Clear emotional contrast between panels\n   - Body language: Confident vs. defeated or surprised postures\n   - Environmental details: Perfect vs. imperfect settings\n   - Props and objects: Idealized vs. realistic versions\n\n6. **Humor Theory & Psychological Triggers**\n   - Incongruity theory: Unexpected contrast between expectation and reality\n   - Superiority theory: Audience feels smart for recognizing the truth\n   - Relief theory: Shared experience reduces individual anxiety\n   - Self-deprecating humor: Allows audience to laugh at common struggles\n   - Universal experiences: Situations most people can relate to\n   - Timing and surprise: Visual punchline delivered effectively\n\n7. **Brand Integration Opportunities**\n   - Subtle product placement in reality panel showing authentic use\n   - Brand colors incorporated naturally into design elements\n   - Logo placement that doesn't interfere with meme authenticity\n   - Brand voice reflected in text tone and humor style\n   - Customer experience themes relevant to brand's industry\n   - Community building through shared brand experiences\n\n8. **Social Media Optimization**\n   - Platform-specific sizing: Instagram, Twitter, Facebook, TikTok compatibility\n   - Thumbnail effectiveness: Clear visual impact at small sizes\n   - Shareability factors: Easy to understand and relate to quickly\n   - Comment-driving elements: Controversial or discussion-worthy comparisons\n   - Hashtag integration: Natural incorporation of trending hashtags\n   - Cross-platform adaptation: Easy modification for different platforms\n\n9. **Viral Mechanics & Engagement**\n   - Immediate recognition: Audience understands format instantly\n   - Personal connection: Viewers see themselves in the scenario\n   - Share motivation: Content worth sharing with friends and followers\n   - Comment triggers: Elements that encourage audience interaction\n   - Remix potential: Template easy to customize with new content\n   - Trend longevity: Format sustainable across multiple trend cycles\n\n10. **Technical Specifications**\n    - Resolution: 4K (3840x3840) for crisp display across all devices\n    - File format: PNG with transparency options for overlay flexibility\n    - Color space: sRGB for consistent social media display\n    - Compression: Optimized for fast loading without quality loss\n    - Template layers: Separate layers for easy text and image customization\n    - Font licensing: Commercially licensed fonts for brand usage\n\n11. **Content Customization Framework**\n    - Industry-specific versions: Healthcare, education, retail, technology\n    - Demographic variations: Age groups, cultural backgrounds, interests\n    - Seasonal adaptations: Holiday themes, weather-related content\n    - Current events: Trending topics and cultural moments\n    - Brand personality: Formal vs. casual, humorous vs. serious\n    - Campaign integration: Product launches, sales, awareness campaigns\n\n12. **Authenticity & Brand Safety**\n    - Genuine relatability without forced humor or artificial scenarios\n    - Inclusive representation across diverse demographics\n    - Avoiding controversial topics that could damage brand reputation\n    - Cultural sensitivity in humor and visual representation\n    - Age-appropriate content for target audience\n    - Legal compliance with advertising standards and regulations\n\n13. **Performance Metrics & Success Indicators**\n    - Engagement rate: Likes, comments, shares per impression\n    - Reach expansion: Organic sharing beyond initial audience\n    - Brand mention increase: Tagged usage and brand association\n    - Website traffic: Click-through rates from meme to brand content\n    - Conversion tracking: Sales or leads generated from meme campaigns\n    - Sentiment analysis: Positive vs. negative audience response\n\n14. **Campaign Integration & Strategy**\n    - Series potential: Multiple memes building on same theme\n    - User-generated content: Encouraging audience to create variations\n    - Influencer partnerships: Collaboration with meme creators and influencers\n    - Paid promotion: Boosting high-performing organic memes\n    - Cross-channel integration: Email, website, and offline marketing\n    - Long-term brand building: Consistent humor style and voice development\n\nOutput Format: Create a versatile, highly relatable meme template with detailed customization guidelines that brands can use to create authentic, engaging content that drives viral sharing and positive brand association.",
